{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6841ed7d-607f-4813-8e2c-b54ab976dca5","content":"\n\nFor a **Web API project**, common templates and auth options depend on your stack:\n\n### .NET\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual   # Identity-based (JWT bearer)\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg    # Microsoft Entra ID (Azure AD)\ndotnet new webapi --auth MultiOrg     # Multi-tenant Azure AD\ndotnet new webapi --auth Windows      # Windows/Negotiate auth\n```\n\n### Node.js\n- **Express** + Passport.js (JWT, OAuth2, OpenID Connect)\n- **Fastify** + `@fastify/jwt`\n- **NestJS** with Guards (JWT, API keys, OAuth2)\n\n### Python\n- **FastAPI** with OAuth2/JWT (`python-jose`, `passlib`)\n- **Django REST Framework** with TokenAuth or JWT (`djangorestframework-simplejwt`)\n\n### Common Auth Patterns\n| Pattern | Best For |\n|---|---|\n| **JWT Bearer** | SPAs, mobile apps |\n| **OAuth2 / OIDC** | Third-party login (Google, GitHub) |\n| **API Keys** | Service-to-service |\n| **Cookie-based** | Traditional web apps |\n\nWant me to scaffold a specific project? Let me know your preferred stack and auth type.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cc52e7b7-d353-4fab-93b4-1ac8fc1eeff9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - it's a straightforward informational question I can answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":360},"id":"49adce4e-bfd5-458b-828c-aed55ebadb90","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:52:01.679Z","parentId":"b7c28693-7883-44af-a93a-0b9fb3f849be"}
